      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "> Is there a reason we don't read directly into the std::string?\r\n\r\n@luke-jr If I am not wrong, it is not advisable to `fread` into `std::string` as `c_str()` is `const` and we will also need to know the size of the file beforehand to allocate the right number of characters. [More Details](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/13612340/c-fread-into-a-stdstring)\r\n\r\n> Looks like your patch causes a \"global buffer overflow\" in the ASan CI task\r\n\r\n@MarcoFalke fixed the ASan issue in the unit test.\r\n",
